.TH "batadv_check_claim_group" 9 "batadv_check_claim_group" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
batadv_check_claim_group \- check for claim group membership
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" batadv_check_claim_group
.BI "(struct batadv_priv *bat_priv "  ","
.BI "struct batadv_hard_iface *primary_if "  ","
.BI "u8 *hw_src "  ","
.BI "u8 *hw_dst "  ","
.BI "struct ethhdr *ethhdr "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "bat_priv" 12
the bat priv with all the soft interface information
.IP "primary_if" 12
the primary interface of this batman interface
.IP "hw_src" 12
the Hardware source in the ARP Header
.IP "hw_dst" 12
the Hardware destination in the ARP Header
.IP "ethhdr" 12
pointer to the Ethernet header of the claim frame
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
checks if it is a claim packet and if it's on the same group.
This function also applies the group ID of the sender
if it is in the same mesh.
.SH "RETURN"
2  - if it is a claim packet and on the same group
1  - if is a claim packet from another group
0  - if it is not a claim packet
